The height above the subject that the drone attmepts to maintain.

detaileddescription.para: e.g. 15 meters

briefdescription.para: See GetFollowHeightAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The distance from the subject that the drone attempts to maintain.

detaileddescription.para: e.g. 30 meters

briefdescription.para: See GetFollowDistanceAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The maximum distance allowed from the subject before the drone resets to the target position.

detaileddescription.para: e.g. 100 meters

briefdescription.para: See GetMaxDistanceAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The maximum speed the drone is allowed to move.

detaileddescription.para: e.g. 20.0 meters/second

briefdescription.para: See GetMaxSpeedAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The higher the gain, the faster the drone will accelerate towards the target position.
See GetHorizontalVelocityGainAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The higher the gain, the higher the climb or descent rate of the drone to get to the target altitude.
See GetVerticalVelocityGainAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The higher the gain, the more closely the drone will match the velocity of the subject and the more connected it will appear.
See GetFeedForwardVelocityGainAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The velocity of the drone is filtered to make it appear as if it is accelerating.

detaileddescription.para: e.g. 1.0 seconds

briefdescription.para: See GetVelocityFilterTimeConstantAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: The angular velocity of the drone is filtered to make it appear as if it is accelerating.

detaileddescription.para: e.g. 0.2 seconds

briefdescription.para: See GetRotationFilterTimeConstantAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: An offset vector from the subject origin at which the drone looks.
See GetPositionOffsetAttr(), and also Usd_Create_Or_Get_Property for when to use Get vs Create.

detaileddescription.para: If specified, author defaultValue as the attribute's default, sparsely (when it makes sense to do so) if writeSparsely is true - the default for writeSparsely is false.

briefdescription.para: Applies this single-apply API schema to the given prim.

detaileddescription.para: This information is stored by adding "PhysxCameraDroneAPI" to the token-valued, listOp metadata apiSchemas on the prim.

simplesect.para: A valid PhysxSchemaPhysxCameraDroneAPI object is returned upon success. An invalid (or empty) PhysxSchemaPhysxCameraDroneAPI object is returned upon failure. See UsdPrim::ApplyAPI() for conditions resulting in failure.

briefdescription.para: Returns the type of schema this class belongs to.
